import React from "react"; import Footer from "./Footer"; import Title from "./Title"; class Register extends React.Component { render() { return ( <>
<div> <p style={{ color: "#b2b2b2", textAlign: "left", fontSize: "20px" }}> Welcome to #tech!<br></br><br></br> We provide You with the latest releases of smart phones, laptops, PCs and more, all at a reasonable price. We cater to You. <br></br><br></br> In order to become our customer, please fill out the registration form. All fields are required. </p> </div> </div> <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 align-self-center mx-lg-2" > <div style={{ textAlign: "left" }}> <div class="form-group"> <Title fontSize="50px" fontWeight="lighter" color="#b2b2b2" text="Registration Form" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="NAME" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="LAST NAME" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="ADDRESS" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="EMAIL" /> <br></br> <input type="password" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="PASSWORD" /> <br></br> <input type="password" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="CONFIRM PASSWORD" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="PHONE" /> <br></br> <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-lg" placeholder="CREDIT CARD" /> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <Footer /> </> ); } } export default Register;
